Reasoning: The paper deals with the online variant of the minimum dominating set problem, which is a fundamental problem in graph theory and combinatorial optimization. The problem is defined on undirected graphs, and the paper specifically focuses on trees. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), and cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory). The paper also discusses the design of algorithms, which suggests that it could belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
